          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Ya I admit every big organisations have there own positive sides and also downsides.  I got admitted in this school in the year 2012 in class 4 and this year c9mpleated my class 12 . I have seen and witnessed many things from police to protests but it's my school I love it . I have hated my teachers for asking me for my homework but also love them because unlike other school they were like my family.  Specally  I enjoyed my class 11 and 12 as it was when I got the chance to know my teachers closely . I use to fear my Bengali teacher in class 9 and 10 as she was very strict but in real world she is very friendly . From sharing our lunch to doing childish stuff all was supported by her . I would like to tell all those who say that the teachers of my school r not good that there is no school where u can get teacher like this school . Here they scold u but when u cry they also comfort u , support u  this is the only school I have see my teachers caring a injured student and admiring them in hospitol then calling there pairents , even when my pairents where scared for me passing class 10 my teachers trusted me , my maths/class  teacher trusted me.  I cannot finish telling the stories of all the fun I had in my school with all my ultra strict but family like teachers and friends . Once a wise artst( me😂) said , my school life was a painting which had both black and also whit in it but I'll miss it 😌",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
